Contact me

You can use this form to ask me about collaborations, consultations, speaking engagements, if you have thoughts, ideas, suggestions, or questions about any of my education resources.

Note to those interested in joining the lab:

Currently, our lab is only looking for undergraduate students. My primary projects center on scientific communication and the creation and assessment of computer-based learning tools for biology, experimental design, and statistics. As a result, I am only looking for undergraduates that have a basic skill set in one or both of these areas.

Interested in writing? Send me at least one example of writing that you are particularly proud of. Bonus points for it being published somewhere publicly available (e.g., Saltman Quarterly, an online blog).

Interested in creating learning tools? You must have completed my BILD 5 course successfully OR have taken a comparable class in the R computing language.

You’re in the driver’s seat. I am here to support your ideas and help you find viable projects that YOU have ownership over. You won’t be doing my busywork and you’ll have the opportunity to gain confidence in your problem-solving and critical thinking skills. It’s up to you whether your work get’s published, presented, or shared online.



If you are in the UCSD area or want to send me something via mail, my mailing address is:
